---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <nav
        class="w-full px-8 py-6 flex justify-between items-center border-b border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10"
    >
        <a
            href="/#work"
            class="text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors"
            >← Back to Home</a
        >
        <h1
            class="text-sm font-serif-elegant tracking-wide text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
        >
            Saurabh Sawant
        </h1>
    </nav>

    <main class="min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center w-full pb-32">
        <header class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 pt-24 pb-16">
            <p
                class="text-xs tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-4"
            >
                Master Thesis · Feb 2026 - Aug 2026
            </p>
            <h1
                class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-serif-elegant text-slate-900 dark:text-white leading-tight mb-8"
            >
                Articulated Motion Planning for Dual-Body Non-Holonomic Mobile
                Robots
            </h1>

            <div
                class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-white/10 pt-8"
            >
                <span>ROS 2</span><span>•</span><span>Nav2</span><span>•</span
                ><span>C++</span><span>•</span><span>Graph SLAM</span><span
                    >•</span
                ><span>Kinematics</span>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 mb-16 flex justify-center">
            <img
                src="/Janus_simulation.png"
                alt="Project Overview"
                class="w-full h-auto max-h-[70vh] object-contain rounded-2xl shadow-sm dark:shadow-none opacity-90 bg-slate-100 dark:bg-[#111]"
            />
        </div>

        <article
            class="w-full max-w-6xl px-8 text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-300 font-light leading-relaxed space-y-12 text-lg text-justify mt-8"
        >
            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Literature Review & Requirements
                </h3>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Research & Modeling:</strong
                        > Conducting a comprehensive narrative literature review on
                        motion planning, kinematic modeling, and control approaches
                        for articulated and non-holonomic mobile robots.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Dual-Body Focus:</strong
                        > Focusing specifically on dual-body platforms formed by two
                        differential-drive units and investigating established techniques
                        such as lattice-based planning, Hybrid-A*, and articulated-kinematic
                        modeling.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >System Criteria:</strong
                        > Defining comprehensive functional requirements and necessary
                        criteria for kinematic consistency, articulation-aware trajectory
                        generation, and collision avoidance based on these findings.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Framework Adaptation & MRG-SLAM Integration
                </h3>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Nav2 Architecture:</strong
                        > Adapting an existing ROS 2-based navigation framework to
                        handle the non-holonomic constraints of dual-body systems.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Localization:</strong
                        > Leveraging an existing multi-robot graph simultaneous localization
                        and mapping (MRG-SLAM) algorithm to maintain robust mapping.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Hinge-Aware Mechanics:</strong
                        > Extending specific components to natively support an articulated
                        motion model, including hinge-aware collision checking and
                        specialized trajectory planning strategies.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Implementation & Physical Deployment
                </h3>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >ROS 2 Integration:</strong
                        > Implementing the adapted framework directly within a ROS
                        2 environment by actively integrating planning modules and
                        articulation-state mechanisms into the Navigation2 (Nav2)
                        stack.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Hardware Deployment:</strong
                        > Deploying the navigation components onto the physical dual-body
                        robotic hardware.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Low-Level Communication:</strong
                        > Adapting robot interfaces, verifying communication with
                        low-level controllers, and ensuring compatibility with the
                        onboard MRG-SLAM system to prepare for real-world experimental
                        validation.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
                <h3
                    class="text-base font-bold tracking-widest text-teal-900 dark:text-amber-400 uppercase mb-6"
                >
                    Validation & Experimental Analysis
                </h3>
                <ul
                    class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 marker:text-teal-900 dark:marker:text-amber-400"
                >
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Simulation & Real-World Trials:</strong
                        > Validating the framework and internal dependencies through
                        extensive simulations and controlled outdoor experiments.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >Quantitative Metrics:</strong
                        > Performing validation using metrics such as trajectory fidelity,
                        hinge evolution, and collision-free operation to rigorously
                        assess navigation accuracy, articulation dynamics, and obstacle-avoidance
                        behavior.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong
                            class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white"
                            >System Evaluation:</strong
                        > Analyzing experimental results to determine the robustness
                        and practical applicability of the framework, and formulating
                        recommendations for potential extensions to more complex articulated
                        platforms and broader deployment scenarios.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
